h2.heading.heading--secondary#long-words-automatic-word-breaking Long Words: Automatic word breaking

p.paragraph
  :markdown-it
    The `.word-break` mixin asks the browser to break long words automatically.
    In the best case the browser breaks only syllables and adds appropriate hyphens,
    though this is subject to the used browser's implementation it helps if you specifiy the `lang` attribute.
    See:
     - [CanIUse css-hyphens](http://caniuse.com/#feat=css-hyphens)
     - [CanIUse word-break](http://caniuse.com/#feat=word-break)

+example('/components/demos/long-words-automatic-word-breaking.html')

